  "text": "A graph G = (V, A) is bi-directed if each arc a ∈ A has an anti-parallel twin in A as well. For an arc a = u → v, let a := v → u be its reversal. Let n = |V | and m = |A|. It was shown that cluster-popping can take exponential time in general [CITATION_1] while in bi-directed graphs, the expected number of resampled variables is at most",
